## Testing plan

- `build` gate: `dotnet build Berreman.slnx -c Release` from `Berreman/` MUST pass with the new UI modules and storage `$def` fills compiling; the UI builds against the public MIT `Avalonia.FuncUI` NuGet, NOT the audit-gated clone.
- `unit-tests` gate: `dotnet test --no-build -c Release` from `Berreman/BerremanTests/` stays green (this slice does not touch `BerremanTests`).
- `constructor-unit-tests` gate (project `OpticalConstructor.Tests`, slice 001): MUST pass and increase the count over the prior baseline.
  - `StackEditTests.fs` — add/delete/reorder/duplicate/group yield the expected `films : List<Layer>` (`Media.fs:98`) with engine `Layer`/`OpticalSystem` records unmutated (AC-B5); medium selectors set `upper`/`lower` `OpticalProperties` (`Media.fs:97,100`) preserving `films`/`substrate` (AC-B6); substrate switch sets `None`/`Some (Plate _)`/`Some (Wedge _)` (`Media.fs:99`) and re-solving routes through the existing `OpticalSystemSolver` substrate branch (`Solvers.fs:201-230`) unchanged (AC-B7).
  - `ProjectJsonRoundtripTests.fs` (extended) — beam tree + systems round-trip through the JSON-canonical `OpticalConstructorProject` validated against `optical-constructor-project.schema.json`, with no FsPickler/`.binz` write (AC-B9).
  - AC-B1: a construction-page `BeamNode` solve obtains `reflected`/`transmitted` via the reused `OpticalSystemSolver` (`Solvers.fs:199`) reading `Solution.emSys` (`Solvers.fs:156`), with no forked solver in `OpticalConstructor.Domain.fsproj`.
  - AC-B10: deleting a node with children presents a pre-confirmation gate stating the live-derived descendant count, and structural edits refresh dependent views from the new `EmFieldSystem` without manual reload (model/`update` testable without Avalonia per P3).

## Risks

- **Medium.** The construction page is the first real MVU surface and the integration point where the slice-002 domain (beam tree, routing), the slice-003 storage (`$defs`/round-trip), and the slice-004 materials (resolved `OpticalProperties`) all meet; a missing or mismatched seam shows up only here. Mitigation: keep the model/`update` Avalonia-free (P3) so the edit transformations and the descendant-count/refresh logic are unit-tested without a UI; consume — never reconstruct — the beam-tree types and the resolved tensors; fill the `$defs` field-level shapes without renaming the Part A anchors; confirm no `.binz` write path is reachable from the construction page and no FuncUI-clone reference is introduced.

## Hand-off

The Part B UI construction layer exists: the stack/layer editor over `OpticalSystem.films`, the incident/exit medium selectors, the three-state substrate switch, and the top-level construction page with its destructive-edit UX, per-node busy, and results refresh — plus the beam-tree-and-systems JSON round-trip filling the `beamNode`/`beamBranch`/`opticalSystem`/`layer`/`unitOfMeasure` `$def` field-level shapes. Slice 006 (Part C) adds the curved-element domain (lenses & non-flat mirrors). Emit the state-of-the-world file with all required ATX headings (`Where we are`, `What's working`, `Tests`, `Architecture`, `Deferred`, `Gotchas`, `Changelog`) and a fenced `gates:` YAML baseline block carrying the updated `constructor-unit-tests` count so the next slice's `count_at_least` gate has a baseline.
